BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 1: The Psychology of Clutter) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Clutter is not just a physical problem. It affects your mental health daily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Studies show cluttered spaces increase cortisol, the stress hormone, in your body.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Visual clutter competes for your attention and reduces your ability to focus.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (People in cluttered homes report higher levels of anxiety and depression.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Clutter often represents unmade decisions that weigh on your subconscious mind.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (We keep things out of guilt, fear, or a sense of obligation to the past.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Sunk cost fallacy makes us keep things because we spent money on them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (The just in case mentality fills our homes with items we never actually use.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Clutter accumulates slowly over years until it feels overwhelming.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Understanding why you hold onto things is the first step to letting go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (You are not your stuff. Your memories exist in your heart, not in objects.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A clear space creates a clear mind and room for what truly matters to you.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (1) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
