BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 85.44 600 Td (Chapter 2: Getting Started Mindset) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start with the understanding that decluttering is a process, not a single event.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Do not try to declutter your entire home in one weekend. You will burn out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Begin with a small area like a single drawer to build momentum and confidence.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Set a timer for 15 minutes and declutter until it rings. Then stop or continue.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Progress over perfection. Done imperfectly is better than never started.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (You will not regret getting rid of things. Research shows people feel relief.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Take before and after photos to motivate yourself and track your progress.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Enlist a supportive friend or family member if you need accountability.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Avoid buying organizing products before decluttering. Reduce first, then organize.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Expect emotional resistance. It is normal to feel attached to belongings.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Remind yourself that someone else could benefit from items you never use.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (You deserve to live in a space that supports your current life and goals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (2) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
