BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 112.32000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 3: The 4-Box Method) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Get four boxes or bags and label them: Keep, Donate, Trash, and Relocate.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Every single item you touch must go into one of these four categories.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Keep means the item earns its place in the room and you use it regularly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Donate means the item is in good condition but no longer serves your life.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Trash means the item is broken, expired, stained, or cannot be given away.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Relocate means the item belongs in a different room of your home.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Handle each item only once. Pick it up, decide, place it in a box, move on.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (If you hesitate more than five seconds, ask: have I used this in the past year?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (If the answer is no and it has no sentimental value, it goes in donate or trash.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (At the end of each session, immediately take donate bags to your car.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Take trash bags out right away so items do not creep back into your home.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (The 4-box method removes decision fatigue by simplifying your choices.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (3) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
