BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 4: Decluttering the Kitchen) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Start with expired food in the pantry, fridge, and freezer. Toss without guilt.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Remove duplicate utensils. You do not need four spatulas and six wooden spoons.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Donate gadgets you used once or never: bread makers, fondue sets, and specialty pans.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Keep only the dishes and glasses your household actually uses daily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Clear countertops of appliances you use less than once a week.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Consolidate food storage containers and match lids. Recycle orphaned pieces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Remove expired spices which lose potency after two to three years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Donate cookbooks you never open. Most recipes are available free online now.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Keep one good set of pots and pans and donate cheap duplicates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Organize the junk drawer by removing true junk and keeping only functional items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Toss stained dish towels, worn sponges, and chipped mugs or plates.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A clean, clear kitchen makes cooking enjoyable rather than stressful.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (4) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
