BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 5: Decluttering the Bedroom) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Your bedroom should be a peaceful retreat for rest and relaxation only.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Remove anything that does not support sleep: work papers, exercise equipment, clutter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Clear nightstands to only essentials: lamp, book, water glass, and phone charger.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Under the bed should be empty or contain only one flat storage container.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Remove excess decorative pillows that you toss on the floor every night anyway.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Pare down to two sets of sheets per bed. You only need one on and one washing.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Donate extra blankets and comforters you have not used in over a year.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Clear dresser tops of accumulated items that have no specific home.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Remove old magazines, mail, and papers that have accumulated in the bedroom.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Keep bedroom surfaces clear and you will sleep better and feel calmer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (A minimalist bedroom with less visual stimulation promotes deeper rest.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Your bedroom should make you feel relaxed the moment you walk in.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (5) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
