BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 77.75999999999999 600 Td (Chapter 6: Decluttering the Bathroom) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Check expiration dates on all medications and dispose of expired ones safely.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Makeup expires: mascara after 3 months, foundation after 12, lipstick after 18.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Toss old toothbrushes, dried-out nail polish, and rusty razors immediately.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Remove sample-size products you collected from hotels but never use.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Keep only products you use in your current routine, not aspirational purchases.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Consolidate half-used bottles of the same product into one container.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Donate unopened, unexpired products to local shelters that accept toiletries.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Remove excess towels. Keep two bath towels and two hand towels per person.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Clear the shower of bottles you have not touched in the last month.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Organize under the sink by removing products and keeping only what you use.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (A decluttered bathroom feels like a spa and your morning routine becomes faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Clean bathrooms are easier to maintain when there are fewer items to move.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (6) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
