BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 66.24000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 7: Decluttering the Living Room) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (The living room should invite relaxation and connection, not visual chaos.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Remove magazines and newspapers older than one month. Recycle them today.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Assess decorative items: do they bring joy or just collect dust?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Keep surfaces mostly clear with only one or two meaningful decorative pieces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Remove DVDs, CDs, and books you have watched, listened to, or read already.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Donate board games, puzzles, and toys that no one has played in over a year.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Corral remote controls, chargers, and small items in one attractive basket.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Remove throw pillows and blankets beyond what you actually use for comfort.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Assess furniture: does every piece serve a purpose and fit the space?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Remove items that belong in other rooms and put them where they go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Clear entertainment center surfaces and hide cords for a clean look.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (A simplified living room feels larger, calmer, and more welcoming to guests.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (7) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
