BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 85.44 600 Td (Chapter 8: Decluttering the Closet) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Remove everything from your closet and only put back items you truly wear.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (If you have not worn something in 12 months, donate it regardless of condition.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Try the hanger trick: turn all hangers backward, flip forward when worn.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (After six months, donate everything still on backward-facing hangers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Keep only clothes that fit your current body, not your aspirational size.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Donate duplicates. You do not need fifteen white t-shirts or eight black pants.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Remove clothes with stains, holes, or missing buttons that you never repair.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Keep a small capsule wardrobe of pieces that mix and match easily.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Organize remaining clothes by category: tops, bottoms, dresses, outerwear.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Donate shoes that hurt your feet no matter how much they cost originally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (A streamlined closet makes getting dressed in the morning fast and enjoyable.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (You will feel like you have more clothes when you can actually see everything.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
