BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 54.72 600 Td (Chapter 12: What to Do with Unwanted Items) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Donate usable items to thrift stores like Goodwill, Salvation Army, or local charities.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Many charities offer free home pickup for large donations. Schedule online.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Sell valuable items on Facebook Marketplace, Craigslist, or Poshmark.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Host a garage sale for a quick way to clear many items at once.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Give items to specific people you know would appreciate and use them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Buy Nothing groups on Facebook connect you with local neighbors who want items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Freecycle.org lets you post free items for local pickup by people who need them.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Recycle electronics at dedicated e-waste collection events or retailers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Textile recycling accepts clothing too worn for donation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Hazardous items like paint and chemicals go to community collection events.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Do not let the decision of where to send items stop you from decluttering.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Speed matters: get items out of your home within 48 hours of deciding to let go.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (12) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
