BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 50.879999999999995 600 Td (Chapter 13: Maintaining a Clutter-Free Home) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Maintaining is easier than the initial declutter if you build simple habits.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Do a ten-minute tidy every evening: put everything back in its designated spot.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Process mail daily: recycle junk, file important items, pay or schedule bills.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Make your bed every morning. This one habit sets a tone for the entire day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Clean as you go: put things away immediately rather than setting them down.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Do a weekly fifteen-minute sweep of each room to catch accumulation early.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Schedule seasonal thirty-minute declutter sessions for each room quarterly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Assign a home for every item in your house. If it has no home, it is clutter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Reset your home to its baseline state before going to bed each night.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Involve all household members in maintaining shared spaces equally.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Habits take 30 to 60 days to form. Be patient and consistent with yourself.) Tj ET
