BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 81.6 600 Td (Chapter 14: The One-In-One-Out Rule) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (This simple rule prevents clutter from ever building up again after decluttering.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (When one new item enters your home, one similar item must leave.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Buy a new shirt? Donate an old one you no longer wear or love.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Receive a gift? Release something you own that serves the same purpose.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (This forces intentional purchasing: is this item worth removing something else?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (The rule applies to books, clothes, kitchen items, decorations, and toys.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Over time you naturally become more selective about what you bring in.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Quality replaces quantity. You buy fewer but better items that last longer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Keep a donation bag in your closet to add items to throughout the month.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (When the bag is full, drop it off at your nearest donation center immediately.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (This rule is especially powerful for families with children who receive many gifts.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (One-in-one-out transforms decluttering from a big project to an effortless lifestyle.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (14) Tj ET

endstream
